                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm will *never* be as safe as a rogue or wizard for the group, so we're already screwed I'd say. Here are my thoughts on it anyway:
<br />

<br />
Charm dps should be higher then a single other pc, just not so much higher that the other classes arent viable anymore. If you have to choose between a (imaginary numbers) 400dps rogue, 350dps wizard or 500dps charm pet (that randomly kills the group) the choice isnt nearly as clear as the situation that is fresh in everyone's mind, Vxed or Tipt. Also, there should always be a risk with charm - if it's possible to negate it effectively entirely the other classes are screwed again (that probably means charm blocking snare - fine with me if that means it gets balanced).
<br />

<br />
I dont really like the idea of preventing hasting pets, haste gives you the opportunity to tailor the risk you take to the reward. if the risk isnt entirely negated anyway (hey look, snare) hasting is a very huge increase in risk and gives a proper reward.
<br />

<br />
So I guess I want an increase in risk by removing snare, making the pet summon, or whatever else they can think of, and in return I want to keep the ability to match or beat a dps classes' dps in exchange for the risk that is being taken. Force me to deal with the pet using my own abilities (and provide those abilities, WoM, non-nerfed color stun) instead of a rangers and the risk is already going up significantly, because I have to face the dps the pet does. Running from a snared mob to gain distance to cast is hardly a risk and that's the problem with Tipt/vxed. But instead of taking steps to fix the risk portion they left it the same and took a sledgehammer to the reward side.
<br />

<br />
Current OoW charm is a miserable crutch, I can do similar dps with nuking and dont have to take any risks for it - WHY would I use charm? And even if they lowered risk so far that charm is viable - it's still barely better then nuking then and very low risk, if I wanted that I'd be a mage.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7110" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jennifer DeGartes</a>, Enchantress of <a href="http://www.vazaelle.dk" target="_blank" class="postlink">Caer Cadarn</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
